Chronic sleep deprivation can lead to cardiovascular issues and mortality, as shown in recent studies.
Research indicates that insufficient sleep can stress the heart and increase the risk of diseases.
Shift workers and early risers are particularly vulnerable due to disrupted sleep patterns.
Athletes and students often overlook the importance of adequate rest, impacting their performance.
Sleep deprivation affects memory, appetite, and weight gain, with potential links to obesity and hypertension.
Addressing sleep problems, especially in adolescents, may help prevent substance use.
Further research is needed to understand the full impact of sleep deprivation on overall health.
